<br>
::What is girls?<br>
<br>
Antare, one of the priestesses, spoke up.<br>
<br>
::Goddess, something's wrong.  We were going after one of the icons when we met some resistance.  Mythen and I took care of things, but the bodies didn't stay down!!  We tried to dispatch them again, but they just got up.  We know their dead, and they acted liked animated corpses.<br>
<br>
The other priestesses nodded in agreement.  They had all experienced the same thing.<br>
<br>
::Girls, Hades and Thanatos have joined us.  But their doing it their own way. Hades has forbidden souls from entering Tartarus and Thanatos has forbidden beings from dying.  So now, these bodies are caught in a limbo-state.  They're not exactly dead, but also not exactly alive.  Their souls are no longer within their bodies.  So what we have here are roaming spirits and living corpses.  But if you are all saying that the bodies are still attacking you, then that means the bodies are still sentient.  This makes things a bit more dangerous.  You can't kill them, but they can hurt you.  Use your own judgement.<br>
<br>
With that the priestesses and Hecate blinked out, returning to their hunt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hecategoddessofmagic>Hecate Goddess of Magic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/11/03 12:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nefaria.com/gallery/1152x864/art/sorceress1152.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Who else</span><hr size=1> With what was going on, Hecate and her priestesses were having a much harder time accomplishing their goals.  At first, Hecate was just going to go about accomplishing her tasks without any aid from her brethern.  But now, she realized that she had better rethink her plan.<br>
<br>
The fact that many of the other gods were missing, or hadn't made an appearance troubled Hecate.  What could they be up to?  Were they going to be a problem in the future?<br>
<br>
For instance, Ares, hadn't even uttered a peep throughout all this.  Hecate would have bet money that Ares would have been everywhere.  He is the God of War, and what greater war could there be besides the one they were currently in?  A war between the Titans, rulers of old, and the Olympians, the present rulers.<br>
<br>
And what of his ilk?  Malice loves bloodshed of which there is plenty of.  The Furies fueled the fire of war.  And since it may come down to the slaying of certain Titans, which also happens to be the parents of some of the gods, the Furies would have a field day with all this.  To them the killing of ones parents was the worse act they could imagine.  And what about Nemesis and Eris?<br>
<br>
Hecate felt for sure that she would have to visit Hephaestus.  There were certain Titans that had to be recaptured, if they had managed to escape.  And there were certain Titans that the gods have to make sure never do.  For example, if Atlas manages to leave his post, the world would tumble head-first into oblivion.  Therefore, the gods would surely have to call upon the skills of Hephaestus once again.<br>
<br>
The question of who allowed the Titans to escape was still unanswered.  Hecate didn't want to point fingers...not just yet, but she had a hunch that once again, Ares wouldn't be too far behind.  If so, the need for Athena would be required.  She always managed to balance out Ares.<br>
<br>
Currently, where are the missing Titans?  To find them, the gods would need two of the best sleuths, Apollo and Artemis.  These two godlings circled the world consistently, day and night.  If the Titans dared to poke their heads out of their hiding holes, these two would surely spot them.<br>
<br>
What about the deep?  Many of the ocean's denizens are direct descendants of Titans.  So could they be hiding there now?  Apollo and Artemis would have a hard time looking into the depths.  Therefore it would be up to Poseidon.  Hecate didn't think Poseidon was a suspect.  But Poseidon held no love for Athena.  And since Ares didn't either, there could be a chance these two were working together, but that all goes back to IF Ares was the cause.<br>
<br>
Hecate's head hurt just thinking about who else was missing and who could be involved.  She just hoped that those who are working towards their cause continues to, and those that can would join.  Hopefully, they wouldn't end up doing the Titans job for them.<br>
